		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Hotkeys,and group ettiquite for Bards<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Hotkeys,and group ettiquite for Bards";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Oct 4th 8:29 PM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1096936143479297875&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1096936143479297875&num=2&post=1&replyto=1096936143479297875"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=230592"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=1096936143479297875></a></small>| <span id="fs8">Edited: 2004-10-04 20:31:46</span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=230592"><span id="">esoterique</span></a><b><span id=""></span></b><br />30 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.33]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=esoterique&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>This is an informative guide, designed for newbies to the bard class, who are just getting started on twisting, and pulling. <br /> <br />Once you are ready to start serious grouping - meaning you are actually pulling difficult mobs to your group, who will stay in one place, or are following a room behind in the case of a LDON adventure <br />In the case of my &quot;group/ldon&quot; hotkey map:&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />I set 1 as my <b>pull key</b>, generally something as simple as  <br /> <br />Incoming &lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; %T &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;, Assist me now! (One add per message) <br /> <br />is sufficient. You would hit that key once for the first target, and once more for any additional mobs you pick up along the way. %T is the command for target - so whatever you have targeted will show up there. (such as an Orc, Lady Vox, Etc.) It gives the group time to gear up and get ready to do one of a few things: <br /> <br /><b>Off-tank</b> - which means someone distracts that extra mob <br /><b>Peel-and-park </b> - which means someone will draw the add away, and root it. <br /><b>Kite</b>- which if you are a bard, should be fairly easy to figure out. <br /><b>Mezz/Charm</b> - again, sort of obvious. In many cases, you ARE the Mezzer - so this lets the group know to try and give you some space. <br /><b>Succor/Evac</b>- In some cases, certain zones can be too hard if you get an add. This really only applies to higher level groups. <br /> <br />So. Long story short - let the group know you are pulling, what it is, and how many. <br /> <br />Keys 2-5 are my battle songs. Generally, lower level bards will have trouble keeping up 4 songs at once - even I have trouble juggling when I get a lot of lag - so shoot for 2 songs first. The most useful tools in learning to twist are: <br /> <br />--Your casting bar <br />--The ability to type, without looking at the keys <br /> <br />When I was learning, I found that spell messages were helpful in determining if a song &quot;hit&quot; or not - now I just watch my casting bar, and song window.  <br /> <br />WHAT the heck is &quot;twisting&quot;? Well - when using hotkeys with this map, you will go in a cycle, from 2-5. so, assuming it takes 3 seconds to cast each song, your key pattern will look like this: <br /> <br />2 (3 second pause) 2, 3 (3 second pause) 3,4 (3 second pause) 4, 5 (3 second pause) 5, 2  <br /> <br />and so on. In the beginning, you may find it hard to time - this is where the casting bar comes in to play. Watch until the casting bar is fully empty, and starts to fade, then quickly tap a key to stop the song ( I prefer the key of what I just cast ), and then tap the key of the song that you want to cast next. Again - in the beginning, song fizzles ( You miss a note, bringing your song to a close ) will really slow you down, so stick to the first two, rather than the first 4 song slots.  <br /> <br />Generally, I keep the first 4 &quot;song&quot; slots (2-5) fairly simple -  <br /> 2: Haste song <br /> 3: Mana/Hp regen song <br /> 4: Damage shield song <br /> 5: Target slow/snare <br /> <br />The following slots are used when I pull, or to help the others in the group.: <br /> <br /> 6: Resist song <br /> 7: Pulling song ( Important: try to get into the habit of using songs that don't damage the target - at higher levels the target may summon you. I like to use Occulsion of Sound, or Disspell. ) <br /> 8: Mezz song  <br /> 9: Charm song, or Divine Aura song <br />  <br />Of course, if you are lower-level, you may not have all the songs above. If you don't, just experiment, and see what you seem to use the most.  <br /> <br />and as for my 0 hotkey slot - I have an &quot;assist&quot; key set up. so... <br /> <br /> 0: Assist ( /assist nameoftank ) <br /> <br />In higher level groups, it is very important to assist your tank. You might be able to kinda tank at level 5, but then again, so can a level 5 wizzie. Kinda. At level 48, you will still tank as well as a 45 wizzie.. which means you are about as tough as a lemon is sweet. The other important thing to do when /assisting, is to turn of the autoattack component - otherwise, you may break a mezz spell, or draw aggro from the mob before the tank, which can result in anything from a really annoyed mezzer, to a total wipe. So, remember. <b>/assist off.</b> <br /> <br />Any thoughts? Please let me know.  <br /> <br />--Aria <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Mon Oct  4 20:30:32 2004 by esoterique</span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Mon Oct  4 20:31:46 2004 by esoterique</span></i></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />--Arianea Rhapsody</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >2 Replies</td></tr></table>
