		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Oct 17th 11:09 PM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1096936143479297875&num=2&post=1&replyto=1098068946142175708"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1098068946142175708></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=257523"><span id="">CptGotoh</span></a><b><span id=""></span></b><br />15 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=CptGotoh&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Excellent post. I personally used about 4 separate hotkey windows at level 32. 1 was miscellaneous (like crafts), 1 was combat songs, 1 was noncombat songs, and the fourth was gsay's for battle messages (eg pulling, healing, incoming, etc.). I wasn't all that hardcore of a gamer, either. <br /> <br />If you're going to be hardcore, you should probably have about 5 windows dedicated just to songs and gsays, each window a combination of both depending on what you're doing for the group, or if you're soloing. <br /> <br />EG at lower levels, you could have a tank window, a charmer window, a restorer window, and a flee window, as well as a solo window.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Gozvin, the Half-Elven Bard <br />Rantok, the Ogre (tall Dwarf dammit!) Warrior</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from A deeper shade of blue.</td></tr></table>
