		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id="Scholar">Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1943 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.19]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>My general setup for my 64 bard: <br /> <br />NOTES: <br />a) ` (key to the left of 1) is an alternate key for 9 <br />b) F2 is toggle through NPCs, nearest first <br />c) TAB is toggle last target <br />d) q is alternate for 7 <br />e) w is alternate for 8 <br /> <br />Hotbank 1 (downtime): <br /> <br />1- spell gem 1 (mana/hp regen) <br />2- /sit <br />3- /afk <br />4- forage hotkey <br /> <br />Hotbank 2 (CR): <br /> <br />1- spell gem 1 (selos) <br />2- /corpse <br />3- spell gem 2 (selos travel) <br />4- spell gem 3 (invis for indoors) <br />5- spell gem 4 (levitate for indoors) <br />6- spell gem 5 (kazumi's [divine aura]) <br />7- Fading memories <br />8- /disc deftdance <br />9- /shout TRAIN TO ZONE, MAKE A HOLE!! <br />0- tracking <br /> <br />Hotbank 3 (group/solo): <br /> <br />1- spell gem 1 <br />2- spell gem 2 <br />3- spell gem 3 <br />4- spell gem 4 <br />5- spell gem 5 <br />6- /g ASSIST me on %t, it's not a fan of my music! <br />7- fading memories <br />8- /disc deftdance <br />9- /assist [mt's name] if grouping, /pet attack if soloing <br />0- tracking <br /> <br />Keep in mind that this is at level 64. It's completely flexible, and it will most definately be different for you in lower levels, considering you won't have the nifty aa's and /discs. One of the ones I had for group early on was /g mezzing %t. It seems a lot of people in the lower levels don't even know that bards can mez, and will proceed to pound on your mezzed adds unless you announce it to them. They should understand in the higher levels though and it's usually not needed to announce it. <br /> <br />I like to keep my hotbanks as similar as possible. When something bad happens, you don't want to have to look at the hotbank to hit that key that's going to save your life. <br /> <br />I have more spellsets saved the hotbanks. I think I have 7 spells sets for all kinds of different situations. To save a spell set, right click the spell book and select &quot;save spellset&quot;, name it, then when you need to remem that spell set, right click the spell book and select the spell set you want. <br /> <br />The most important aspect to barding is knowing your songs. You'll hear people complain in the higher levels that they're tired of twisting the same 4 songs all the time... that's true to a point, but if you analyze the strengths and weaknesses of your groups, there's usually a song or 2 you can switch out for a better overall effect. <br /> <br />My &quot;typical&quot; group twist (when pulling): <br />1- mana/hp <br />2- PoV (all resists up and DS) <br />3- Rizlona's (overhaste and DD/DoT focus) <br />4- Warsong of Zek (V1 haste that doesn't stack with chanter/shaman, STR, DS) <br />5- SSoQ (lull) <br />6- OoS (unresistable MR/FR/CR debuff, used to pull) <br />7- RoT (1 min slow) or snare/slow (3 sec duration) <br />8- selos (if outdoors) or whatever I feel like playing with <br /> <br />The bard is the most flexible class in EQ, and you have the tools to do a lot of things. We are THE jack of all trades. We aren't master of anything, but we can do almost EVERTHING pretty damn well. We can fill in for any role in a group, save main tank (aggro holding problems) and main healer (no burst heals, just a low HP regen).</p>
